  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Customer Review Officer-Financial Crime Compliance",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Duties</strong></u></p><p>1.   Perform end to end   know-Your-Customer (KYC) Onboarding/Periodic/Trigger Reviews, as a Checker for financial institutions, Retail and Corporate Banking customers. </p><p>2.   Ensure all higher risk cases have been identified, escalated and relevant approvals have been obtained.</p><p>3.   Review customers’ Source of Wealth (SOW), including assessing documentation and producing well-structured SOW narratives. </p><p>4.   Review and clear Daily Name Screening alerts. </p><p>5.   Investigate and file Internal Suspicious Transaction Reports (ISTR) to Financial Crime Compliance Department  (FCCD) on suspicious customers and transactions.</p><p>6.  Perform ad-hoc assessment on escalations from Business Units to determine whether Trigger Reviews are  required.</p><p>7.  Provide ad-hoc advisory for Business Units on KYC related matters.</p><p>8.  Participate in assigned projects and process improvement initiatives. <br /></p><p><u><strong>Requirement</strong></u></p><p>•    University graduate with not less than 5 years of relevant experience in the financial services industry.  </p><p>•     Sound knowledge of MAS regulatory requirements (e.g., MAS Notice 626) and AML/CFT Industry Partnership (ACIP) best practices.</p><p>•     ACAMS certification or ICA AML qualification will be an advantage.</p><p>•     Strong analytical skills and detailed-oriented.</p><p>•     Proactive and able to work independently.</p><p>•     Good verbal and written communication skills.</p>",
